# keycloack Development Guidelines

Auto-generated from all feature plans. Last updated: 2026-05-04

## Active Technologies

- **Backend services** (`ms-auth`, `ms-products`, `ms-payments`): Java 25 (LTS) + Spring Boot 4.0.6 (Spring MVC + virtual threads)
- **Kong custom plugin** (`jwt-keycloak-validator`): Lua 5.1 / LuaJIT — Kong OSS 3.9.1
- **IdP**: Keycloak 26.6.1 (`quay.io/keycloak/keycloak:26.6.1`), `start-dev --import-realm`
- **Plugin cache**: `kong.cache` em-processo (L1 worker LRU + L2 nginx shared dict). Sem cache externo.
- **Orchestration**: Docker Compose v2
- **Build (Java)**: Maven (per-service `pom.xml`)
- **Java HTTP client**: Spring `RestClient` + `@HttpExchange` interfaces
- **In-process cache (ms-auth JWKS)**: Caffeine (TTL 60s)
- **Tests — Java**: JUnit 5 + Mockito + AssertJ; Testcontainers (Keycloak module) for integration
- **Tests — Lua**: busted + kong-pongo
- **Tests — E2E / load**: Newman 6.x; k6 0.51+

